            <h2>Instruments Info</h2>
            <p><strong>Trombone</strong> <br><br>
            <head><meta name="keywords" content="trombone,saxaphone,elongated">
<meta name="description" content="Instruments information" </head>
                The trombone is a predominantly cylindrical tube bent into an elongated "S" shape. Rather than being completely cylindrical from end to end, the tube is a complex series of tapers with the smallest at the mouthpiece receiver and the largest just before the bell flare. The design of these tapers affects the intonation of the instrument. As with other brass instruments, sound is produced by blowing air through pursed lips producing a vibration that creates a standing wave in the instrument. <br><br>
