<p><strong>Violin</strong><br>
The violin, also known as a fiddle is a string instrument, usually containg four strings. It is the smallest/ highest pitched instrument of the "violin" family. A musician that plays a violin is callled a violinist. sounds can be produced from a violin by drawing  a bow across the string or even by plucking them. The violin is played by musicians across a range of genres. </p>
