<p><strong>Piccolo</strong>
<br>
The piccolo is half the size of a flute and a member of the woodwind family. The piccolo has the same fingerings as a standard flute. but the sound it produces is higher than that of the flute. The name given to it is Italian which stands for "Little octave" </p>
